#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.59"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.59:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.59:0.2"
msgid "6. Dukkhavagga"
msgstr "6. Suffering"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.59:0.3"
msgid "59. Viññāṇasutta"
msgstr "59. Consciousness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.59:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.59:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Saṃyojaniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu assādānupassino viharato viññāṇassa "
"avakkanti hoti."
msgstr ""
"“There are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on "
"the gratification provided by these things, consciousness is conceived."

msgctxt "sn12.59:1.3"
msgid "Viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Consciousness is a condition for name and form. …"

msgctxt "sn12.59:1.4"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.59:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahārukkho."
msgstr "Suppose there was a great tree."

msgctxt "sn12.59:2.2"
msgid "Tassa yāni ceva mūlāni … pe …"
msgstr "And its roots going downwards and across all draw the sap upwards. …"

msgctxt "sn12.59:2.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyesu dhammesu assādānupassino viharato "
"viññāṇassa avakkanti hoti … pe …."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are things that are prone to being fettered. When you "
"concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, consciousness is "
"conceived. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.59:3.1"
msgid ""
"Saṃyojaniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato viññāṇassa "
"avakkanti na hoti."
msgstr ""
"There are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on "
"the drawbacks of these things, consciousness is not conceived."

msgctxt "sn12.59:3.2"
msgid "Viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When consciousness ceases, name and form cease. …"

msgctxt "sn12.59:3.3"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.59:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahārukkho."
msgstr "Suppose there was a great tree."

msgctxt "sn12.59:4.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya … pe …"
msgstr "Then a person comes along with a spade and basket. …"

msgctxt "sn12.59:4.3"
msgid "āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""
"In this way the great tree is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, "
"obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "sn12.59:4.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyesu dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato "
"viññāṇassa avakkanti na hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are things that are prone to being fettered. When you "
"concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, consciousness is not conceived."

msgctxt "sn12.59:4.5"
msgid "Viññāṇassa nirodhā nāmarūpanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When consciousness ceases, name and form cease. …"

msgctxt "sn12.59:4.6"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.59:4.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
